1.title: Moving In
1.plot: Moving day arrives for Justin, but he finds two characters already living in his new home.

2.title: Housewarming
2.plot: After getting comfortable in his new home, Justin wants to throw a housewarming party, but Little Monster is in a cheeky mood and Robert the Robot has turned the heating up to full.

3.title: The Tidy Prize
3.plot: Robert is delighted that Chris is coming to visit, but worries whether he will be able to keep the house tidy.

4.title: Robert's Inventions
4.plot: Robert's invention suddenly changes everyone's hair colour, so Nina sets out to create an antidote to turn things back to normal.

5.title: Bake That Cake
5.plot: Justin enlists Little Monster's help to bake a cake for Robert.

6.title: Auntie Justina Visits
6.plot: When Auntie Justina decides to drop by Justin's House everyone tries their best to stay clean and tidy.

7.title: Suits You Justin
7.plot: Justin gets his best suit dirty while playing football, and tries to wash it before going out.

8.title: Race Day
8.plot: Justin plans to ride his old bicycle Zoomer to victory on Race Day, and hopes to beat his friends.

9.title: Little Monster's Bath
9.plot: Robert and Justin try to give Little Monster her monthly bath.

10.title: Starting with Art
10.plot: Little Monster and Justin argue when they both want to use the same materials to paint with.

11.title: Get Fit Justin
11.plot: Robert invents the "Jigglometer 3000" to ensure that Justin keeps on the move and gets fit.

12.title: Pandamonium
12.plot: Nisha and her friends Mish, Moosh and Mogo visit the house.

13.title: Robert Gets Converted
13.plot: Robert invents a machine for changing the sounds of things.

14.title: Robert's Holiday
14.plot: Justin decides to send Robert on a vacation as he is so hardworking, but the robot is reluctant to go.

15.title: The Bloomer's Plant
15.plot: Robert and Just decide to clear and recycle around the house, and get things ready for Mr Bloom.

16.title: Blocked Pipes
16.plot: Justin and Robert try to find out what is blocking the pipes and, after discovering the culprit.

17.title: Cousin Cuddle
17.plot: Justin entertains children with singing, dancing and comedy, assisted by Robert the robot.

18.title: The Singing Lesson
18.plot: Justin thinks Robert's friend Jodie is coming round for a singing lesson, but ends up being taught how to perform a song brilliantly by the visitor, who is already a great singer.

19.title: The Sleepover
19.plot: Things go bump in the night when Mr Maker comes to stay Justin's House.

20.title: The Wishing Wardrobe
20.plot: Justin is very excited to discover a fancy dress day is taking place in Justin Town.

21.title: Little Monster & the Box of Tricks
21.plot: Nisha tries to help cheer up Little Monster when Justin and Robert notice he is not his usual self.

22.title: Little Pot of Brothers
22.plot: Can Little Monster saves the day when Mr Bloom's special seed grows out on control.

23.title: All Wrapped Up
23.plot: Robert and Little Monster prepare the house for the festive season, but Justin's efforts to help cause problems.

1.title: Hottyspottyitis
1.plot: Justine and Little Monster need help from Doctor Download and Robert Robot when they catch Hottyspottyitis. Every-time they sneeze something messy happens in Justin's House!

2.title: Little Monster's Birthday
2.plot: Little Monsters birthday party gets very messy when Justine, Robert, Chris and Pui all join in the celebrations.

3.title: Superturbo Robo
3.plot: Justin decides Robert needs some help with the housework and gives him a helping hand with the Roberta the Superturbo Robo!

4.title: Going for Gold
4.plot: Justin's house hosts the first ever Justinship Games, and Justin dreams of winning a gold medal.

5.title: The Mystery Pong
5.plot: Justin and Robert must find where the mystery pong is coming from before their friend Nina arrives at the house.

6.title: House for Sale
6.plot: Justin wants to sell his house but Robert and Little Monster have other ideas and concoct a plan to stop Justin from selling it.

7.title: Back in Time
7.plot: Justin takes everyone on a time traveling adventure when he builds a time machine and transports everyone back in time.

8.title: Posh Nosh
8.plot: Justin wants to treat Roberta the Superturbo Robo and Robert to dinner, but things dont go to plan when Justin's Cake-a-pulter Hundred Thousand machine breaks down.

9.title: Just the Part
9.plot: Mayhem ensues when Chris and Pui decide Justin's House is the perfect setting for their new play.

10.title: The Snow Monster
10.plot: A snow monster has been spotted up the mountain and Justin decides to go looking for it.

11.title: Best in Show
11.plot: The Wheely Good trophy is the star prize at the Justin Town Vehicle Show. Justin and Robert do their best to get Justin's car ready to be judged by the mystery star judge.

12.title: Zooper Dooper
12.plot: When the heating at the Justin Town Zoo breaks down Justin decides to bring some of the animals home for a day to two.

13.title: Just in Space
13.plot: The race is on in Justin's house to fill the one remaining space in the Justin Town Space Mission.

14.title: The House of Justin
14.plot: When Justin's House opens its doors as a department store, Wild Adventures presenter Andy Day tries to buy some of the bargains on offer.

15.title: Just for Fun
15.plot: When Mister Maker brings the fair to Justin's house, a very cheeky little ghost gets loose from the Ghost Train ride.

16.title: Justin Rocks
16.plot: Rock star Justin and his new band try to get ready in time to open the first ever Justinbury Music Festival.

17.title: Justin's House Hotel
17.plot: After opening his house as a hotel, Justin and Robert do their best to make the house look like a proper hotel while the first guest dozes upstairs.

18.title: Monster Sitting
18.plot: Robert wants to go to the Grand Robot Ball, but he can only go if he finds someone to look after Little Monster - and Justin!

19.title: Just in a Dream
19.plot: Robert invents a dream machine to discover the funny thing that Justin is dreaming about.

20.title: Justin Times
20.plot: Andy Day helps Justin and Robert attempt to print a newspaper called the Justin Times.

21.title: The Tooth Fairy
21.plot: Everyone hopes the Tooth Fairy will visit Justin's house when one of Little Monster's teeth falls out.

22.title: Just Tins of Paint
22.plot: Can Justin's attempt at home improvements be enough to win Mister Maker's Makeover Challenge?

23.title: Little Monster's Den
23.plot: Things get messy when Justin and Robert try to make Little Monster a gingerbread den.

24.title: Robert's Memory Download
24.plot: Justin, Robert and Little Monster have great fun remembering funny things that happened in Justin's house when Robert downloads his memory bank.

25.title: Pie Cam
25.plot: With the help of Little Monster's new invention the 'Pie Cam' Justin, Robert and Dee Livery look back and laugh all over again at some of the messiest times in Justin's house.
